            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-7 col-md-push-5">
                    <h2>Exchanging Barriers</h2>
                    <p>78% of ESRD patients are candidates for at-home PD based on clinical criteria. However, current utilization in the U.S. is less than 10%.<sup>8-10</sup></p>
                    <p>Contributing factors include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>A need to increase financial incentives for at-home dialysis</li>
                        <li>Physician and nurse training</li>
                        <li>Lack of patient education about therapeutic options</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The cost of managing CKD is significant, but offering at-home PD doesn’t mean spending more. The annual per-patient cost of PD is 16% lower than hemodialysis.<sup>1</sup></p>
                </div>
